  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of fiduciary duty and trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. White-collar crimes of this nature require a sentence that provides general deterrence to others in similar positions of trust. However, the court heavily weighs the mitigating factors present in this case: the defendant has no prior criminal record, and they have already demonstrated remorse and taken responsibility by partially returning the stolen funds. A lengthy period of incarceration would be counterproductive, as it would severely hinder the defendant's ability to maintain employment and pay the remaining restitution owed to the victim. Therefore, a short period of incarceration is appropriate to reflect the seriousness of the offense, which will be followed by supervised probation to ensure the complete repayment of the embezzled funds.",
  "verdict": 6
}
